      <sec id="Sec7">
        <title>Stationary distribution of the number of semi-urgent slots waiting</title>
        <p>At the start of every week the state of the system is inspected. We represent the system by a slotted queuing model in discrete time [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR16">16</xref>]. We can distinguish between two situations: (1) more semi-urgent slots are waiting than can be completed in one week (epochs 2&#x2013;6 and 9 in Fig.&#xA0;<xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>), and (2) less (epoch 7 in Fig.&#xA0;<xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>) or an equal amount of semi-urgent slots are waiting (epoch 8 in Fig.&#xA0;<xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>) than can be completed. We obtain the following expressions for the transition probabilities:
