				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \begin{array}{rll} A&amp;=&amp;\{w=(w1,w2): w1,w2=0,1,\ldots; \\ &amp;&amp;w1\leq m; w1+w2\leq 2m\}. \end{array} $$\end{document}</tex-math><graphic xlink:href="10729_2010_9127_Article_Equl.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>The state space is depicted in Fig.&#xA0;<xref rid="Fig3" ref-type="fig">3</xref>. The areas <italic>B</italic>,<italic>C</italic> and <italic>D</italic> and the arrows correspond to the three different cases of handling the overtime slots (see also Fig.&#xA0;<xref rid="Fig2" ref-type="fig">2</xref>). For notational purposes, let
<disp-formula id="Equm"><alternatives><tex-math id="M27">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
