<fig id="Fig2"><label>Fig.&#xA0;2</label><caption><p>Number of semi-urgent slots performed in overtime: three different cases</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="10729_2010_9127_Fig2_HTML" id="d28e1719"/></fig><fig id="Fig3"><label>Fig.&#xA0;3</label><caption><p>State space of the system</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="10729_2010_9127_Fig3_HTML" id="d28e1728"/></fig></p>
          <p>If <italic>w</italic>1<sub><italic>n</italic></sub>&#x2009;&lt;&#x2009;<italic>m</italic> and <italic>w</italic>1<sub><italic>n</italic></sub>&#x2009;+&#x2009;<italic>w</italic>2<sub><italic>n</italic></sub>&#x2009;&lt;&#x2009;2<italic>m</italic> then no slots are performed in overtime in week <italic>n</italic> and thus we have
