          <p>Analogously, if at the start of week <italic>n</italic> the number of waiting semi-urgent slots is described by <italic>w</italic>&#x2009;&#x2208;&#x2009;<italic>C</italic>, then the next state is <italic>w</italic><sub><italic>n</italic></sub>&#x2009;=&#x2009;(<italic>m</italic>,<italic>m</italic>), and thus the transition probabilities for this state are given by
<disp-formula id="Equp"><alternatives><tex-math id="M31">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
